                            <comment id="15192225" author="ijuma" created="Sun, 13 Mar 2016 08:50:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=becket_qin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;becket_qin&quot;&gt;becket_qin&lt;/a&gt;, are you intending to work on this (double-checking if you forgot to assign it to yourself to avoid duplicating work).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15192535" author="becket_qin" created="Sun, 13 Mar 2016 21:19:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ijuma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ijuma&quot;&gt;ijuma&lt;/a&gt; I am currently blocked on this issue and working on this. Besides the issue in reported in this ticket, the batch expiration checking code seems not following the design in KIP-19. We are supposed to let each retry have a separate request timeout, but the code doesn&apos;t seem doing so. I will submit the patch shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
